    {
      "segment_id": "7e5c5a39",
      "source_content": "With recent production deployments from Facebook and Twitter, I think a new trend is slowly growing: atomic CSS-in-JS.",
      "source_content_hash": "0b50883e91190c71adbea7b57a4218da6e24b3cb9d8a47e9addcb6bfb0e32100",
      "node_type": "paragraph",
      "translatable": true,
      "translations": {
        "zh-hant": "隨著 Facebook 和 Twitter 最近的生產部署，我認為一個新趨勢正逐漸興起：原子化 CSS-in-JS。"
      },
      "invalid_translations": {}
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "8d66f911",
      "source_content": "In this post, we'll see what atomic CSS is, how it relates to functional / utility-first CSS like TailwindCSS, and that big players are adopting it in their modern React codebases.",
      "source_content_hash": "da9bc93e3d149c10868604d36a5e2b5f70f781da9bb772228608a8c512f4fe21",
      "node_type": "paragraph",
      "translatable": true,
      "translations": {
        "zh-hant": "本文將探討何謂原子化 CSS、它與功能性／工具優先 CSS（如 TailwindCSS）的關聯，以及大型企業如何在現代 React 程式碼庫中採用此技術。"
      },
      "invalid_translations": {}
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "ad8fd492",
      "source_content": "As I'm not a expert of this subject, don't expect a deep dive about the pros and cons. I just hope you get an idea about what it's about.",
      "source_content_hash": "c55b38c1dc33fd94859ab6748a82a2b53d380d18ff4533e40c8725f014383265",
      "node_type": "paragraph",
      "translatable": true,
      "translations": {
        "zh-hant": "由於我並非此領域專家，請勿期待深入的優缺點分析。僅希望能讓您對此概念建立基本認知。"
      },
      "invalid_translations": {}
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "86b54d44",
      "source_content": "**Note**: Atomic CSS is not really related to [Atomic Design](https://atomicdesign.bradfrost.com/).",
      "source_content_hash": "adb4e0c83b661d8784e1e1f8c2777ade319c232e4aca70c1fd595d1a979359cc",
      "node_type": "paragraph",
      "translatable": true,
      "translations": {
        "zh-hant": "**注意**：原子化 CSS 與 [Atomic Design](https://atomicdesign.bradfrost.com/) 並無直接關聯。"
      },
      "invalid_translations": {}
